  <summary date="2008-05-06T16:11:04Z" status="Introduced in Senate">BPA-Free Kids Act of 2008 - Treats as a banned hazardous substance under the Federal Hazardous Substances Act any consumer product that contains a detectable amount of bisphenol A (commonly known as BPA) and that is designed for or intended for use by, or care of, a child seven years of age or younger. Permits state laws that provide equal or greater protection.

Requires a study on the health effects of BPA exposure in all age groups and in pregnant women.</summary>
